Mildred MORRELL v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4650. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. March 30, 1953. Robert E. Holland, Denver, Colo., for appellant. Robert A. Sauer, Acting General Counsel, A. M. Edwards, Jr., Asst. General Counsel, Nathan Siegel, Solicitor, and Isa-dore A. Honig, Sp. Litigation Attorney, Office of Rent Stabilization, Washington, D. C., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and PICKETT, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of ap-pellee, for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
